Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase and all existing features. Let me look at one more thing to finalize my proposal:Based on my thorough analysis of the entire codebase, I can see:

- **Speaking tab**: 15 card types (speak, shadow, opinion, story, follow-up, idiom, question, explain, role-play, tongue twister, rapid fire, sentence stress, register switch, debate, scene description)
- **Listening tab**: 7 card types (dictation, listen-respond, listen-paraphrase, minimal pairs, listening comp, spot-error, predict-next)
- **Dictation**: word-for-word transcription of single sentences (typing)
- **Shadow**: repeat single sentences immediately
- **ListenAndSummarize**: summarize a passage (Listening page post-quiz only)
- **Echo Practice**: sentence-by-sentence repetition (Listening page post-quiz only)

The clear gap: **No dictogloss-style exercise** тАФ a proven SLA technique where learners listen to a multi-sentence passage at normal speed, then reconstruct the content from memory by speaking. This is fundamentally different from dictation (word-for-word typing), shadowing (immediate repetition), and summarization (condensing). Dictogloss forces deep meaning processing and grammatically accurate production from memory.

